—would signal to Havana that there is no diminution in U.S. irritation over the
                    Angolan intervention and that we are not impressed by claimed troop
                    withdrawals;

—could risk the nationalization of the ITT facility believed to be the only U.S.
                    business not nationalized in 1960, and deprive us of an interesting argument in
                    future negotiations on compensation;
